Gee, Mike, you must be confused about the MX situation.  It was a year
ago that we had to wait a little while longer.  Or was it two years?
How do I make a smiley face?

While we might not want to try to force everyone out of the stone age in
the next week, we should try to turn up the pressure.  One way to do
this would be to convert some of our larger mailing lists to MX only.
Lets say as a start that we move the bind mailing list to bind@MX, where
MX is an MX-only domain name of some flavor, prohibit "%" and "!" on the
left hand side of the @ for outgoing mail for the list, and site the
list on an host which uses MX but doesn't rewrite on the outgoing side.
Then namedroppers, then tcp-ip, then info-ibmpc, ...  (This would also
give clear research relevance to some suspect lists.)

paul

